dummyPosts.title: Ben Stein
dummyPosts.content: The first step to getting the things you want out of life is this: Decide what you want.

dummyPosts.title: Gloria Pitzer
dummyPosts.content: About the only thing that comes to us without effort is old age.

dummyPosts.title: James Dean
dummyPosts.content: Dream as if you'll live forever. Live as if you'll die today.

dummyPosts.title: Gabriel Coco Chanel
dummyPosts.content: Youth is something very new: twenty years ago no one mentioned it.

dummyPosts.title: Ella Wheeler Wilcox
dummyPosts.content: All love that has not friendship for its base, is like a mansion built upon sand.

dummyPosts.title: Benjamin Disraeli
dummyPosts.content: Great services are not canceled by one act or by one single error.

dummyPosts.title: Audrey Hepburn
dummyPosts.content: I was born with an enormous need for affection, and a terrible need to give it.

dummyPosts.title: Mother Teresa
dummyPosts.content: It's not how much we give, but how much love we put into giving.

dummyPosts.title: Euripides
dummyPosts.content: When love is in excess it brings a man no honor nor worthiness.

dummyPosts.title: Alan Watts
dummyPosts.content: Never pretend to a love which you do not actually feel, for love is not ours to command.

dummyPosts.title: Mahatma Gandhi
dummyPosts.content: Hate the sin, love the sinner.
